        <p><strong>Apple Inc.</strong> is an American multinational corporation head quartered in Cupertino, California, that designs, develops, and sells consumer electronics, computer software and personal computers.</p>
        <p>It is best-known hardware products are the <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Mac', 'ITH'); ?> line of computers, the <strong>iPod</strong> media player, the <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('iPhone', 'ITP'); ?> smartphone, and the <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('iPad', 'ITH'); ?> tablet computer.</p>
        <p>Its consumer software includes the <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('OS X', 'OS'); ?> and <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('iOS', 'MD'); ?> operating systems, the <strong>iTunes</strong> media browser, the <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Safari', 'WB'); ?> web browser, and the iLife and iWork creativity and productivity suites.</p>
        <p>Apple was founded by {<?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Steve Jobs', 'P'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Steve Wozniak', 'P'); ?>, and <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Ronald Wayne', 'P'); ?> on 1 April 1976 to develop and sell personal computers. It was incorporated as <strong>Apple Computer Inc</strong> on 3 January 1977, and was renamed as Apple Inc. on 9 January 2007 to reflect its shifted focus towards consumer electronics.</p>
